This paper focuses on algorithmic fairness and the development of a new measure called multicalibration. It discusses the process of learning a predictor from data and how discrimination can be introduced in this process. Given this focus, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses computational complexity and learning models, which suggests possible sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
